<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=87&amp;p=480#p480</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=87&amp;p=480#p480"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Tile/Graphic Editor Question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=87&amp;p=480#p480"><![CDATA[
YY-CHR is a good editor, it has options to reorganize the tiles in various modes too, which works with graphics for some games.<br /><br />If you want to edit the actual screen, you'll need to modify the tilemap (nametable) data.  Since they all use different formats for it, usually only level editors for specific games can do it (easily).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Wed Dec 08, 2004 11:09 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
